        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Is it still going to fail?\r\n\r\nNo - it looked from the question like you were doing this as a way of calling a regular function in a `nogil` block. If it's marked as `nogil` then it's fine.\r\n\r\nI know internally fused functions use some generated Cython code which does require the GIL to select which function to call. Therefore, I wouldn't expect `f = greater` to work. I think `f = greater[double]` should work though?\r\n\r\n",
