            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "It works if you specify the function pointer type:\r\n\r\n```\r\nctypedef double (*func_ptr)(double, double) nogil\r\n\r\n# then later...\r\ncdef func_ptr f = greater[double]\r\nreturn f(1.0, 2.0)\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt does seem like it should be able to work out the type like it does without fused types though.",
